  38 version_re_str = (
  39     r"(?P<major>\d+)(?:\.(?P<minor>\d+))?(?:\.(?P<patch>(?<=\.)[0-9]+))?\.?"
  40     r"(?:(?P<prerel>[abc]|rc|dev)(?:(?P<prerelversion>\d+(?:\.\d+)*))?)"
  41     r"?(?P<postdev>(\.post(?P<post>\d+))?(\.dev(?P<dev>\d+))?)?"
  42 )
  43 version_re = re.compile(version_re_str)
  44 
  45 
  46 PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATIONS = (
  47     "python",
  48     "ironpython",
  49     "jython",
  50     "pypy",
  51     "anaconda",
  52     "miniconda",
  53     "stackless",
  54     "activepython",
  55     "pyston",
  56     "micropython",
  57 )
  58 if os.name == "nt":
  59     KNOWN_EXTS = {"exe", "py", "bat", ""}
  60 else:
  61     KNOWN_EXTS = {"sh", "bash", "csh", "zsh", "fish", "py", ""}
  62 KNOWN_EXTS = KNOWN_EXTS | set(
  63     filter(None, os.environ.get("PATHEXT", "").split(os.pathsep))
  64 )
  65 PY_MATCH_STR = r"((?P<implementation>{0})(?:\d?(?:\.\d[cpm]{{0,3}}))?(?:-?[\d\.]+)*[^zw])".format(
  66     "|".join(PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATIONS)
  67 )
  68 EXE_MATCH_STR = r"{0}(?:\.(?P<ext>{1}))?".format(PY_MATCH_STR, "|".join(KNOWN_EXTS))
  69 RE_MATCHER = re.compile(r"({0}|{1})".format(version_re_str, PY_MATCH_STR))
  70 EXE_MATCHER = re.compile(EXE_MATCH_STR)
  71 RULES_BASE = [
  72     "*{0}",
  73     "*{0}?",
  74     "*{0}?.?",
  75     "*{0}?.?m",
  76     "{0}?-?.?",
  77     "{0}?-?.?.?",
  78     "{0}?.?-?.?.?",
  79 ]
  80 RULES = [rule.format(impl) for impl in PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATIONS for rule in RULES_BASE]
  81 
  82 MATCH_RULES = []
  83 for rule in RULES:
  84     MATCH_RULES.extend(
  85         ["{0}.{1}".format(rule, ext) if ext else "{0}".format(rule) for ext in KNOWN_EXTS]
  86     )

  89 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
  90 def get_python_version(path):
  91     # type: (str) -> str
  92     """Get python version string using subprocess from a given path."""
  93     version_cmd = [
  94         path,
  95         "-c",
  96         "import sys; print('.'.join([str(i) for i in sys.version_info[:3]]))",
  97     ]
  98     subprocess_kwargs = {
  99         "env": os.environ.copy(),
 100         "universal_newlines": True,
 101         "stdout": subprocess.PIPE,
 102         "stderr": subprocess.PIPE,
 103         "shell": False,
 104     }
 105     c = subprocess.Popen(version_cmd, **subprocess_kwargs)
 106     timer = Timer(SUBPROCESS_TIMEOUT, c.kill)
 107     try:
 108         out, _ = c.communicate()
 109     except (SystemExit, KeyboardInterrupt, TimeoutError):
 110         c.terminate()
 111         out, _ = c.communicate()
 112         raise
 113     except OSError:
 114         raise InvalidPythonVersion("%s is not a valid python path" % path)
 115     if not out:
 116         raise InvalidPythonVersion("%s is not a valid python path" % path)
 117     return out.strip()

 120 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 121 def parse_python_version(version_str):
 122     # type: (str) -> Dict[str, Union[str, int, Version]]
 123     from packaging.version import parse as parse_version
 124 
 125     is_debug = False
 126     if version_str.endswith("-debug"):
 127         is_debug = True
 128         version_str, _, _ = version_str.rpartition("-")
 129     match = version_re.match(version_str)
 130     if not match:
 131         raise InvalidPythonVersion("%s is not a python version" % version_str)
 132     version_dict = match.groupdict()  # type: Dict[str, str]
 133     major = int(version_dict.get("major", 0)) if version_dict.get("major") else None
 134     minor = int(version_dict.get("minor", 0)) if version_dict.get("minor") else None
 135     patch = int(version_dict.get("patch", 0)) if version_dict.get("patch") else None
 136     is_postrelease = True if version_dict.get("post") else False
 137     is_prerelease = True if version_dict.get("prerel") else False
 138     is_devrelease = True if version_dict.get("dev") else False
 139     if patch:
 140         patch = int(patch)
 141     version = None  # type: Optional[Union[Version, LegacyVersion]]
 142     try:
 143         version = parse_version(version_str)
 144     except TypeError:
 145         version = None
 146     if isinstance(version, LegacyVersion) or version is None:
 147         v_dict = version_dict.copy()
 148         pre = ""
 149         if v_dict.get("prerel") and v_dict.get("prerelversion"):
 150             pre = v_dict.pop("prerel")
 151             pre = "{0}{1}".format(pre, v_dict.pop("prerelversion"))
 152         v_dict["pre"] = pre
 153         keys = ["major", "minor", "patch", "pre", "postdev", "post", "dev"]
 154         values = [v_dict.get(val) for val in keys]
 155         version_str = ".".join([str(v) for v in values if v])
 156         version = parse_version(version_str)
 157     return {
 158         "major": major,
 159         "minor": minor,
 160         "patch": patch,
 161         "is_postrelease": is_postrelease,
 162         "is_prerelease": is_prerelease,
 163         "is_devrelease": is_devrelease,
 164         "is_debug": is_debug,
 165         "version": version,
 166     }

 169 def optional_instance_of(cls):
 170     # type: (Any) -> _OptionalValidator
 171     """
 172     Return an validator to determine whether an input is an optional instance of a class.
 173 
 174     :return: A validator to determine optional instance membership.

 181 def path_is_executable(path):
 182     # type: (str) -> bool
 183     """
 184     Determine whether the supplied path is executable.
 185 
 186     :return: Whether the provided path is executable.
 187     :rtype: bool
 188     """
 189 
 190     return os.access(str(path), os.X_OK)

 193 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 194 def path_is_known_executable(path):
 195     # type: (Path) -> bool
 196     """
 197     Returns whether a given path is a known executable from known executable extensions
 198     or has the executable bit toggled.
 199 
 200     :param path: The path to the target executable.
 201     :type path: :class:`~Path`
 202     :return: True if the path has chmod +x, or is a readable, known executable extension.
 203     :rtype: bool
 204     """
 205 
 206     return (
 207         path_is_executable(path)
 208         or os.access(str(path), os.R_OK)
 209         and path.suffix in KNOWN_EXTS
 210     )

 213 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 214 def looks_like_python(name):
 215     # type: (str) -> bool
 216     """
 217     Determine whether the supplied filename looks like a possible name of python.
 218 
 219     :param str name: The name of the provided file.
 220     :return: Whether the provided name looks like python.
 221     :rtype: bool
 222     """
 223 
 224     if not any(name.lower().startswith(py_name) for py_name in PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATIONS):
 225         return False
 226     match = RE_MATCHER.match(name)
 227     if match:
 228         return any(fnmatch(name, rule) for rule in MATCH_RULES)
 229     return False
 230 
 231 
 232 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 233 def path_is_python(path):
 234     # type: (Path) -> bool
 235     """
 236     Determine whether the supplied path is executable and looks like a possible path to python.
 237 
 238     :param path: The path to an executable.
 239     :type path: :class:`~Path`
 240     :return: Whether the provided path is an executable path to python.
 241     :rtype: bool
 242     """
 243 
 244     return path_is_executable(path) and looks_like_python(path.name)

 247 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 248 def guess_company(path):
 249     # type: (str) -> Optional[str]
 250     """Given a path to python, guess the company who created it
 251 
 252     :param str path: The path to guess about
 253     :return: The guessed company
 254     :rtype: Optional[str]
 255     """
 256     non_core_pythons = [impl for impl in PYTHON_IMPLEMENTATIONS if impl != "python"]
 257     return next(
 258         iter(impl for impl in non_core_pythons if impl in path.lower()), "PythonCore"
 259     )

 262 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 263 def path_is_pythoncore(path):
 264     # type: (str) -> bool
 265     """Given a path, determine whether it appears to be pythoncore.
 266 
 267     Does not verify whether the path is in fact a path to python, but simply
 268     does an exclusionary check on the possible known python implementations
 269     to see if their names are present in the path (fairly dumb check).
 270 
 271     :param str path: The path to check
 272     :return: Whether that path is a PythonCore path or not
 273     :rtype: bool
 274     """
 275     company = guess_company(path)
 276     if company:
 277         return company == "PythonCore"
 278     return False

 281 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 282 def ensure_path(path):
 283     # type: (Union[Path, str]) -> Path
 284     """
 285     Given a path (either a string or a Path object), expand variables and return a Path object.
 286 
 287     :param path: A string or a :class:`~pathlib.Path` object.
 288     :type path: str or :class:`~pathlib.Path`
 289     :return: A fully expanded Path object.
 290     :rtype: :class:`~pathlib.Path`
 291     """
 292 
 293     if isinstance(path, Path):
 294         return path
 295     path = Path(os.path.expandvars(path))
 296     return path.absolute()

 307 def normalize_path(path):
 308     # type: (str) -> str
 309     return os.path.normpath(
 310         os.path.normcase(
 311             os.path.abspath(os.path.expandvars(os.path.expanduser(str(path))))
 312         )
 313     )

 316 @lru_cache(maxsize=1024)
 317 def filter_pythons(path):
 318     # type: (Union[str, Path]) -> Iterable
 319     """Return all valid pythons in a given path"""
 320     if not isinstance(path, Path):
 321         path = Path(str(path))
 322     if not path.is_dir():
 323         return path if path_is_python(path) else None
 324     return filter(path_is_python, path.iterdir())

 327 # TODO: Port to vistir
 328 def unnest(item):
 329     # type: (Any) -> Iterable[Any]
 330     target = None  # type: Optional[Iterable]
 331     if isinstance(item, Iterable) and not isinstance(item, six.string_types):
 332         item, target = itertools.tee(item, 2)
 333     else:
 334         target = item
 335     if getattr(target, "__iter__", None):
 336         for el in target:
 337             if isinstance(el, Iterable) and not isinstance(el, six.string_types):
 338                 el, el_copy = itertools.tee(el, 2)
 339                 for sub in unnest(el_copy):
 340                     yield sub
 341             else:
 342                 yield el
 343     else:
 344         yield target

 347 def parse_pyenv_version_order(filename="version"):
 348     # type: (str) -> List[str]
 349     version_order_file = normalize_path(os.path.join(PYENV_ROOT, filename))
 350     if os.path.exists(version_order_file) and os.path.isfile(version_order_file):
 351         with io.open(version_order_file, encoding="utf-8") as fh:
 352             contents = fh.read()
 353         version_order = [v for v in contents.splitlines()]
 354         return version_order
 355     return []
 356 
 357 
 358 def parse_asdf_version_order(filename=".tool-versions"):
 359     # type: (str) -> List[str]
 360     version_order_file = normalize_path(os.path.join("~", filename))
 361     if os.path.exists(version_order_file) and os.path.isfile(version_order_file):
 362         with io.open(version_order_file, encoding="utf-8") as fh:
 363             contents = fh.read()
 364         python_section = next(
 365             iter(line for line in contents.splitlines() if line.startswith("python")),
 366             None,
 367         )
 368         if python_section:
 369             # python_key, _, versions
 370             _, _, versions = python_section.partition(" ")
 371             if versions:
 372                 return versions.split()
 373     return []

 376 def split_version_and_name(
 377     major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 378     minor=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 379     patch=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 380     name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 381 ):
 382     # type: (...) -> Tuple[Optional[Union[str, int]], Optional[Union[str, int]], Optional[Union[str, int]], Optional[str]]  # noqa
 383     if isinstance(major, six.string_types) and not minor and not patch:
 384         # Only proceed if this is in the format "x.y.z" or similar
 385         if major.isdigit() or (major.count(".") > 0 and major[0].isdigit()):
 386             version = major.split(".", 2)
 387             if isinstance(version, (tuple, list)):
 388                 if len(version) > 3:
 389                     major, minor, patch, _ = version
 390                 elif len(version) == 3:
 391                     major, minor, patch = version
 392                 elif len(version) == 2:
 393                     major, minor = version
 394                 else:
 395                     major = major[0]
 396             else:
 397                 major = major
 398                 name = None
 399         else:
 400             name = "{0!s}".format(major)
 401             major = None
 402     return (major, minor, patch, name)

 410 def expand_paths(path, only_python=True):
 411     # type: (Union[Sequence, PathEntry], bool) -> Iterator
 412     """
 413     Recursively expand a list or :class:`~pythonfinder.models.path.PathEntry` instance
 414 
 415     :param Union[Sequence, PathEntry] path: The path or list of paths to expand
 416     :param bool only_python: Whether to filter to include only python paths, default True
 417     :returns: An iterator over the expanded set of path entries
 418     :rtype: Iterator[PathEntry]
 419     """
 420 
 421     if path is not None and (
 422         isinstance(path, Sequence)
 423         and not getattr(path.__class__, "__name__", "") == "PathEntry"
 424     ):
 425         for p in path:
 426             if p is None:
 427                 continue
 428             for expanded in itertools.chain.from_iterable(
 429                 expand_paths(p, only_python=only_python)
 430             ):
 431                 yield expanded
 432     elif path is not None and path.is_dir:
 433         for p in path.children.values():
 434             if p is not None and p.is_python and p.as_python is not None:
 435                 for sub_path in itertools.chain.from_iterable(
 436                     expand_paths(p, only_python=only_python)
 437                 ):
 438                     yield sub_path
 439     else:
 440         if path is not None and (
 441             not only_python or (path.is_python and path.as_python is not None)
 442         ):
 443             yield path

 446 def dedup(iterable):
 447     # type: (Iterable) -> Iterable
 448     """Deduplicate an iterable object like iter(set(iterable)) but
 449     order-reserved.
 450     """
 451     return iter(OrderedDict.fromkeys(iterable))
